.context
# Claude Code state under .claude/ — default-ignore everything, then opt the
# shareable config back in. This is an allowlist on purpose: Claude Code writes
# machine-local runtime files here (credentials, sessions, cache, telemetry,
# scheduler locks, worktrees, …) and new artifact types appear over time, so
# ignoring by default keeps unknown future files out of commits without us
# having to enumerate each one.
#
# NOTE: we ignore the directory's *contents* (.claude/*), not the directory
# itself (.claude/). Git never descends into a fully-ignored directory, so
# ignoring .claude/ would make every negation below a no-op.
.claude/*
# Opt the version-controlled, shareable config back in. Negating a directory
# lets git descend into it; these stay un-tracked until such files exist.
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/hooks/
# Belt-and-suspenders: credentials must NEVER be committed, even if a file lands
# inside one of the re-included directories above. .claude/* only matches direct
# children (not nested paths), and the directory negations re-expose whole
# subtrees — so this final rule (last match wins) re-ignores credentials
# anywhere under .claude/.
.claude/**/.credentials.json
CLAUDE.local.md
# binary build output
/.build/
# Local-build of the fakegithub helper (`make` at repo root drops it here);
# root-anchored so it doesn't shadow the test/fakegithub/ source directory.
/fakegithub
# stray binaries — always build via make build-* into .build/ instead
/cmd/agc/agc
/cmd/gmc/gmc
/cmd/probe/probe
/cmd/proxy/proxy
/cmd/worker/worker
